Class a1.Tile

  • java.lang.Object
    • a1.Tile
  • All Implemented Interfaces:

    public class a1.Tile
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    Tiles for a map.
    Contains a1.Blocks
    Maintains a mapping between exit names and other tiles.

    • Constructor Detail

      • a1.Tile

        public a1.Tile()
        Construct a new tile.
        Each tile should be constructed with no exits (getExits().size() == 0).
        Each tile must be constructed to start with two soil blocks and then a grass block on top.
        i.e. getBlocks() must contain {a1.SoilBlock, a1.SoilBlock, a1.GrassBlock} for a new a1.Tile.

      • a1.Tile

        public a1.Tile(java.util.List<a1.Block> startingBlocks)
     throws a1.TooHighException
        Construct a new tile.
        Each tile should be constructed with no exits (getExits().size() == 0).
        Set the blocks on the tile to be the contents of startingBlocks.
        Index 0 in startingBlocks is the lowest block on the tile, while index N -1 is the top block on the tile for N blocks.
        startingBlocks cannot be null.
        i.e. getBlocks() must contain the contents of startingBlocks, but modifying startingBlocks after constructing the a1.Tile should not change the results of getBlocks().
        Handle the following cases:
        1. If startingBlocks contains more than 8 elements, throw a a1.TooHighException.
        2. If startingBlocks contains an instance of a1.GroundBlock that is at an index of 3 or higher, throw a a1.TooHighException.
        Parameters:
        startingBlocks - a list of blocks on the tile, cannot be null
        Throws:
        a1.TooHighException - if startingBlocks.size() > 8, or if startingBlocks elements with index ≥ 3 are instances of a1.GroundBlock

      • dig

        public a1.Block dig()
          throws a1.TooLowException,
                 a1.InvalidBlockException
        Attempt to dig in the current tile.
        If the top block (given by getTopBlock()) is diggable (block.isDiggable()), remove the top block of the tile and return it.
        Handle the following cases:
        1. Throw a a1.TooLowException if there are no blocks on the tile
        2. Throw an a1.InvalidBlockException if the block is not diggable
        Returns:
        the removed block
        Throws:
        a1.TooLowException - if there are no blocks on the tile
        a1.InvalidBlockException - if the block is not diggable

      • moveBlock

        public void moveBlock(java.lang.String exitName)
               throws a1.TooHighException,
                      a1.InvalidBlockException,
                      a1.NoExitException
        Attempt to move the current top block to another tile. Remove the top block (given by getTopBlock()) from this tile and add it to the tile at the named exit (exitName in getExits()), if the block is moveable (block.isMoveable()) and the height of that tile (the number of blocks given by getBlocks().size()) is less than the current tile *before* the move.
        Handle the following cases:
        • If the exit is null, or does not exist, throw a a1.NoExitException
        • If the number of blocks on the target tile is ≥ to this one, throw a a1.TooHighException
        • If the block is not moveable, throw a a1.InvalidBlockException
        Parameters:
        exitName - the name of the exit to move the block to
        Throws:
        a1.TooHighException - if the target tile is ≥ to this one.
        a1.InvalidBlockException - if the block is not moveable
        a1.NoExitException - if the exit is null or does not exist

      • placeBlock

        public void placeBlock(a1.Block block)
                throws a1.TooHighException,
                       a1.InvalidBlockException
        Place a block on a tile. Add the block to the top of the blocks on this tile. If the block is an instance of a1.GroundBlock, it can only be placed underground. Handle the following cases:
        • If the block is null, throw an a1.InvalidBlockException
        • If the target tile has 8 blocks already, or if the block is a a1.GroundBlock and the target tile has 3 or more blocks already, throw a a1.TooHighException
        Parameters:
        block - the block to place.
        Throws:
        a1.TooHighException - if there are already 8 blocks on the tile, or if this is a ground block and there are already 3 or more blocks on the tile.
        a1.InvalidBlockException - if the block is null
